title: Jeff Bezos' Blue Origin to replace CEO Bob Smith with outgoing Amazon exec Dave Limp
description: Jeff Bezos' Blue Origin will replace CEO Bob Smith with outgoing Amazon exec Dave Limp, CNBC has learned.

title: Merck Covid drug linked to virus mutations that can spread between people, new study says
description: There is still no evidence that molnupiravir, sold under the brand name Lagevrio, has produced more transmissible or severe variants of Covid.

title: Sierra Space raising nearly $300 million from Japanese consortium at $5 billion valuation
description: The fresh funds come as Sierra Space focuses on getting its Dream Chaser spaceplane flying.

title: Microsoft is hiring a nuclear energy expert to help power its AI and cloud data centers
description: Microsoft is looking to hire a nuclear energy expert to help coordinate powering its AI data centers with small nuclear reactors.

title: The first tour inside Manhattan's newest private club, with $100,000 membership fees
description: The new Core Club, spread over four floors above Midtown, is the latest in a wave of elite membership clubs that have opened in major cities since the pandemic.

title: China's outbound travel surges ahead of 'Golden Week' holidays
description: Bookings for foreign destinations such as Singapore and Australia have increased by 20 times compared with the same holiday period last year, Trip.com says.

title: Nissan says all new models launched in Europe will be fully electric
description: The Japanese carmarker said all new models it launches in Europe will be fully electric, as it reaffirmed an aim for all-electric Europe sales by 2030.

title: 'Private equity is now king' for the ultra-rich, says Tiger 21, an exclusive club of investors
description: Tiger 21 members, who manage around $150 billion in assets, have increased their allocation to private equity threefold, founder Sonnenfeldt says.

title: Huawei stays silent on secretive 5G phone at high-profile product launch
description: Chinese telecommunications giant Huawei didn't reveal any details about its new phone or reported advanced chip breakthrough during a high-profile launch event.

title: Saudi Arabian auto rental firm Lumi pops 30% in stock market debut
description: Shares of Lumi soared as much as 30% on Monday at the Saudi Arabian auto rental firm debuted on the Riyadh stock exchange.

title: A top European software investor raises $700 million — defying the venture capital slump
description: Dawn Capital, one of Europe's biggest backers of business-to-business software companies, raised $700 million in two new funds.

title: China property stocks tumble as Evergrande drops 25% on debt restructuring roadblock
description: Chinese real estate giant Evergrande announced it is unable to issue new notes, and rescheduled a debt restructuring meeting with its creditors.

title: Betting on a rate cut now is 'premature,' European Central Bank member says
description: It is "premature" to bet on a cut to interest rates, Francois Villeroy de Galhau, France's central bank governor, told CNBC exclusively on Monday.

title: China-EU relationship is at a crossroads, top official says in Beijing
description: China's relationship with the European Union needs to change, as the bloc's trade chief asks for more openness and fairness from Beijing.

title: Amazon to invest up to $4 billion in Anthropic, a rival to ChatGPT developer OpenAI
description: E-commerce giant Amazon on Monday said it will invest up to $4 billion in Anthropic and take a minority ownership position in the company.

title: CNBC Daily Open: Summer discontent is spilling into the fall
description: UAW strikes could make 2023 the biggest year for labor activity in nearly four decades.

title: Central banks across Europe pause for breath after mammoth rate hike run, but face 'triple dilemma'
description: Several European central banks look set for a pause, but resurgent inflationary pressures and slowing growth may complicate the job ahead.

title: Hollywood writers and studios reach tentative deal to end strike after nearly 150 days
description: Talks between the Writers Guild of America and the Alliance of Motion Picture and Television Producers resumed last week after months of starts and stops.

title: 'Who should I hire? Will I get rich?' Fortune telling is a booming business in Singapore
description: From wealth, to weddings, and who to work with, more and more people are turning to fortune telling in Singapore.

title: Thailand's new prime minister boosts optimism, but his populist policies pose fiscal risks
description: Srettha, Pheu Thai's choice for leader, was appointed prime minister on Aug. 22 and is hoped to bring stability to Thailand’s economy and business environment.

title: Indonesia's EV ambitions could help boost investments in the rest of Southeast Asia
description: Indonesia's EV development is poised to be the "gateway" for further investments in ASEAN, and could play a major role in building the region's EV ecosystem.
